Blocks.childText: IS YOUR LAMP BURNING ? Concluded. 105 A If you thought that they walk'd in the shad - ow, Your lamp would burn brighter, I know. But not ma - ny among them, my broth - er, Shines stead - -i - ly on like a star. N REFRAIN. the Say, is your lamp burning, my broth - er? I pray you look quickly and see; M For if it were burning, then sure - ly Some beam would fall brightly on me. 3 If once all the lamps that are lighted How all the dark places would brighten, Should steadily blaze in a line, How the mist would roll up and away, Wide over the land and the ocean, How the earth would laugh out in her gladness What a girdle of glory would shine ! To hail the millennium day - Refrain.
